# Enable visual feedback (asterisks) during sudo password entry.
#
# Rationale: Sudo's silent default is intended to hide password length
# from shoulder surfers, but an observer who can see the screen
# typically can also hear the keystrokes, exposing both length and
# timing rhythm. Meanwhile, silent input introduces a tangible risk in
# desktop environments: users may believe the terminal has focus while
# another window (chat, meeting client, editor) is actually receiving
# input, leading to inadvertent password disclosure. Visible feedback
# makes such focus mishaps immediately apparent.
#
# Note: CVE-2019-18634 (stack buffer overflow in pwfeedback) was fixed
# in sudo 1.8.31 (January 2020) and does not affect current versions.
Defaults pwfeedback
